info.name: Starter API - v1
info.description:
This is the documentation for Starter API v1 and will be used as the baseline for all Backend App in the future.

Default User Accounts :

```
- SuperAdmin
    u : superadmin_[i]
    p : Admin327E

- Admin
    u : admin_[i]
    p : Admin327E

Notes : 
    i for all accounts are numbers from 1 - 10

Default Login OTP : 327123
Only Superadmin Role that possible to use the Default Login OTP
Other Roles, will using Real OTP that sent to user's email

 ```

Notes for all API resources:

```
- The authentication process is user Log In and API will return Access Token
- Access Token must be included in X-Access-Token headers on all protected resources
- All optional fields must be empty for Json Array and null for non-Json Array (String, Int, Boolean, etc.), if no data submitted
- Read the request description carefully, especially the validation section (length, regex pattern, etc.)
- Every server-side validation must be implemented too in the client-side, except for DB-related validation i.e Unique Validation

 ```
